From Bijan Mobasseri Subject Re Dumbest automotive concepts of all time My ' Ford has vent windows operated by a crank, just like a window only it opened out, like a normal vent window My ' F , my dad's ' Bronco, and pretty much every truck I've seen that's worth riding in has vent windows Does that mean that I'm not a young feller anymore James James P Callison Microcomputer Coordinator, U of Oklahoma Law Center I don't understand the fascination with vent windows They create a tremendous turbulence and noise that makes even a simple connversation impossible at speeds above mph The current flow throuh ventilation, if designed right, are far more superior Bijan